Case 1:20-cr-00330-PAE Document 708 Filed 07/12/22 Page 5 of 15
448:12 - 15 3509-007, p. 3, para 13 Doe was sitting alone on a bench between classes when Epstein and Maxwell approached her. Objection. The defendant did not confront the witness with a specific document.
450:21 - 451:15 3509-028, p. 1 At first tea w/ Epstein, just Epstein, Mom & Jane were present. Objection. The witness agreed with counsel's questions and was not confronted with a document. The Court has already rejected this statement. Tr. 450:8-9.
451:4 - 452:21 3509-001, p. 2, 4th para. In the beginning, Jane would be with her mother and brothers at Epstein's house. No objection.
453:15 - 454:3 3509-003, p. 1, 4th para. Jane was not sure if Maxwell ever called her to make appointments. Objection. Jane said acknowledged and explained the inconsistency. There is no basis for further impeachment.
454:4 - 9 3509-003, p.2, second line When in Florida, Epstein or his office would call Jane's house. Same objection.
455:3 - 18 3509-008, p. 12, 4th paragraph They visited Jane one to two times at her house in Florida. This was about a year or two after meeting him. Objection. Not inconsistent with the witness's testimony, and when confronted with the statement, she said it was correct.
455:19 - 456:13 3509-008, p. 11, last full paragraph At some point Maxwell and Epstein came to Jane's house prior to the abuse. Objection. Not inconsistent with the witness's testimony - see 456:10-13. The Government also notes that the 3500 material makes clear
